# TypeScript + React standards (web/)

- Prefer small pure helpers; keep parsing, graph building, and UI concerns separated.
- Keep types explicit at module boundaries (`ParseResult`, node `data` shapes).
- Avoid O(n^2) scans like `nodes.some(...)` in hot loops when input grows; use maps/sets.
- Keep UI state predictable:
  - Derived graph state comes from `parseK8sYaml(text)` + `buildFlowGraph(parsed)`
  - File import updates text + triggers refresh
- Keep components simple and readable; use consistent typography for “primary vs secondary” fields.
